:"about 1574","1659":"1659","England":"England","Huntingdonshire, England":"Huntingdonshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"elmore","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Ailmer</i>, from Old English <i>Æthelmǣr</i>, composed of the elements <i>æthel</i> ‘noble’ and <i>mǣre</i> ‘famous’. <i>Aylmer</i> has also been established in Ireland since the 16th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellmore","meanings":["English: variant of   Elmore  ."]},{"name":"Elmer","meanings":["English: variant of   Elmore  .","English: habitational name from Elmer in Middleton (Sussex), probably named with Old English <i>ǣl</i> ‘eel’ + <i>mere</i> ‘pool’.","German: topographic name for someone living near elm trees, from Middle High German <i>elm</i> ‘elm tree’."]}]},{"name":"peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705207,"age":11,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705208,"age":13,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705210,"age":26,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"peter elmore was born about 1574, in England as the son of thomas elmore. He had at least 1 son with rebecca harris."},"et":{"about 1574–":"umbes 1574–Surnud","1574–Male":"1574–Surnud","1574–Female":"1574–Surnud","1594–1659":"1594–1659","–Male":"Surnud","1600":"1600","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","1574":"1574","1594":"1594","about 1574":"umbes 1574","1659":"1659","England":"England","Huntingdonshire, England":"Huntingdonshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1574–":"noin 1574–Kuollut","1574–Male":"1574–Kuollut","1574–Female":"1574–Kuollut","1594–1659":"1594–1659","–Male":"Kuollut","1600":"1600","1587":"1587","1585":"1585","1574":"1574","1594":"1594","about 1574":"noin 1574","1659":"1659","England":"England","Huntingdonshire, England":"Huntingdonshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1574–":"environ 1574–Décé